<Link id="l00191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="191"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Calculates a 64-bit to 128-bit multiply, then XOR folds it.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192" lineLink="#ae07c124bf50a0ad869649d3e1d0def90"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint64&#95;t <a href="#ae07c124bf50a0ad869649d3e1d0def90">XXH3&#95;mul128&#95;fold64</a>(uint64&#95;t lhs, uint64&#95;t rhs) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="193"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#if defined(&#95;&#95;SIZEOF&#95;INT128&#95;&#95;) ||                                              \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    (defined(&#95;INTEGRAL&#95;MAX&#95;BITS) &amp;&amp; &#95;INTEGRAL&#95;MAX&#95;BITS &gt;= 128)</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint64&#95;t cross = (lo&#95;lo &gt;&gt; 32) + (hi&#95;lo &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF) + lo&#95;hi;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00564" /><CodeLine lineNumber="564"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00565" /><CodeLine lineNumber="565"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; ==========================================</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00566" /><CodeLine lineNumber="566"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; XXH3 128 bits (a.k.a XXH128)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00567" /><CodeLine lineNumber="567"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; ==========================================</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00568" /><CodeLine lineNumber="568"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; XXH3&#39;s 128-bit variant has better mixing and strength than the 64-bit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00569" /><CodeLine lineNumber="569"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; variant, even without counting the significantly larger output size.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00570" /><CodeLine lineNumber="570"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00571" /><CodeLine lineNumber="571"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; For example, extra steps are taken to avoid the seed-dependent collisions</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00572" /><CodeLine lineNumber="572"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; in 17-240 byte inputs (See XXH3&#95;mix16B and XXH128&#95;mix32B).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="573"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="574"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; This strength naturally comes at the cost of some speed, especially on short</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00575" /><CodeLine lineNumber="575"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; lengths. Note that longer hashes are about as fast as the 64-bit version</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00576" /><CodeLine lineNumber="576"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; due to it using only a slight modification of the 64-bit loop.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00577" /><CodeLine lineNumber="577"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; XXH128 is also more oriented towards 64-bit machines. It is still extremely</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; fast for a &#95;128-bit&#95; hash on 32-bit (it usually clears XXH64).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;!</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @internal</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @def XXH&#95;rotl32(x,r)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @brief 32-bit rotate left.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @param x The 32-bit integer to be rotated.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @param r The number of bits to rotate.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @pre</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;   @p r &gt; 0 &amp;&amp; @p r &lt; 32</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @note</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;   @p x and @p r may be evaluated multiple times.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @return The rotated result.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#if &#95;&#95;has&#95;builtin(&#95;&#95;builtin&#95;rotateleft32) &amp;&amp;                                   \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    &#95;&#95;has&#95;builtin(&#95;&#95;builtin&#95;rotateleft64)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl32 &#95;&#95;builtin&#95;rotateleft32</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl64 &#95;&#95;builtin&#95;rotateleft64</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; Note: although &#95;rotl exists for minGW (GCC under windows), performance seems</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; poor &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#elif defined(&#95;MSC&#95;VER)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl32(x, r) &#95;rotl(x, r)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl64(x, r) &#95;rotl64(x, r)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#else</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605" lineLink="#a70a4b202f9523a2a811da16cde3f52eb"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl32(x, r) (((x) &lt;&lt; (r)) | ((x) &gt;&gt; (32 - (r))))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="606" lineLink="#a056473e50ab5e7acb43d00ca3d41632e"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define XXH&#95;rotl64(x, r) (((x) &lt;&lt; (r)) | ((x) &gt;&gt; (64 - (r))))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00607" /><CodeLine lineNumber="607"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#endif</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="608"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="609" lineLink="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define XXH&#95;mult32to64(x, y) ((uint64&#95;t)(uint32&#95;t)(x) &#42; (uint64&#95;t)(uint32&#95;t)(y))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="610"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="611"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;!</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00612" /><CodeLine lineNumber="612"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @brief Calculates a 64-&gt;128-bit long multiply.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00613" /><CodeLine lineNumber="613"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00614" /><CodeLine lineNumber="614"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Uses &#96;&#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t&#96; and &#96;&#95;umul128&#96; if available, otherwise uses a scalar</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00615" /><CodeLine lineNumber="615"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; version.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00616" /><CodeLine lineNumber="616"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00617" /><CodeLine lineNumber="617"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @param lhs , rhs The 64-bit integers to be multiplied</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00618" /><CodeLine lineNumber="618"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; @return The 128-bit result represented in an @ref XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00619" /><CodeLine lineNumber="619"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00620" /><CodeLine lineNumber="620" lineLink="#a5a010401dcddb43e0a6fdcac9564d69b"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> <a href="#a5a010401dcddb43e0a6fdcac9564d69b">XXH&#95;mult64to128</a>(uint64&#95;t lhs, uint64&#95;t rhs) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00621" /><CodeLine lineNumber="621"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00622" /><CodeLine lineNumber="622"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; GCC/Clang &#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t method.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00624" /><CodeLine lineNumber="624"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; On most 64-bit targets, GCC and Clang define a &#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t type.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00625" /><CodeLine lineNumber="625"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; This is usually the best way as it usually uses a native long 64-bit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; multiply, such as MULQ on x86&#95;64 or MUL + UMULH on aarch64.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00627" /><CodeLine lineNumber="627"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; Usually.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; Despite being a 32-bit platform, Clang (and emscripten) define this type</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; despite not having the arithmetic for it. This results in a laggy</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; compiler builtin call which calculates a full 128-bit multiply.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; In that case it is best to use the portable one.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; https://github.com/Cyan4973/xxHash/issues/211#issuecomment-515575677</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#if (defined(&#95;&#95;GNUC&#95;&#95;) || defined(&#95;&#95;clang&#95;&#95;)) &amp;&amp; !defined(&#95;&#95;wasm&#95;&#95;) &amp;&amp;         \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">        defined(&#95;&#95;SIZEOF&#95;INT128&#95;&#95;) ||                                          \\</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00638" /><CodeLine lineNumber="638"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">    (defined(&#95;INTEGRAL&#95;MAX&#95;BITS) &amp;&amp; &#95;INTEGRAL&#95;MAX&#95;BITS &gt;= 128)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00639" /><CodeLine lineNumber="639"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00640" /><CodeLine lineNumber="640"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> product = (&#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t)lhs &#42; (&#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t)rhs;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00641" /><CodeLine lineNumber="641"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> r128;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00642" /><CodeLine lineNumber="642"><span class="doxyHighlight">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = (uint64&#95;t)(product);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00643" /><CodeLine lineNumber="643"><span class="doxyHighlight">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = (uint64&#95;t)(product &gt;&gt; 64);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00644" /><CodeLine lineNumber="644"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> r128;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00645" /><CodeLine lineNumber="645"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00646" /><CodeLine lineNumber="646"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00647" /><CodeLine lineNumber="647"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; MSVC for x64&#39;s &#95;umul128 method.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00648" /><CodeLine lineNumber="648"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00649" /><CodeLine lineNumber="649"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; uint64&#95;t &#95;umul128(uint64&#95;t Multiplier, uint64&#95;t Multiplicand, uint64&#95;t</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00650" /><CodeLine lineNumber="650"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; &#42;HighProduct);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00651" /><CodeLine lineNumber="651"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00652" /><CodeLine lineNumber="652"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; This compiles to single operand MUL on x64.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00653" /><CodeLine lineNumber="653"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00654" /><CodeLine lineNumber="654"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#elif (defined(&#95;M&#95;X64) || defined(&#95;M&#95;IA64)) &amp;&amp; !defined(&#95;M&#95;ARM64EC)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00655" /><CodeLine lineNumber="655"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00656" /><CodeLine lineNumber="656"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#ifndef &#95;MSC&#95;VER</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00657" /><CodeLine lineNumber="657"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#pragma intrinsic(&#95;umul128)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00658" /><CodeLine lineNumber="658"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#endif</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00659" /><CodeLine lineNumber="659"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t product&#95;high;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00660" /><CodeLine lineNumber="660"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> product&#95;low = &#95;umul128(lhs, rhs, &amp;product&#95;high);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00661" /><CodeLine lineNumber="661"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> r128;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00662" /><CodeLine lineNumber="662"><span class="doxyHighlight">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = product&#95;low;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00663" /><CodeLine lineNumber="663"><span class="doxyHighlight">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = product&#95;high;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00664" /><CodeLine lineNumber="664"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> r128;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00665" /><CodeLine lineNumber="665"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00666" /><CodeLine lineNumber="666"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00667" /><CodeLine lineNumber="667"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; MSVC for ARM64&#39;s &#95;&#95;umulh method.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00668" /><CodeLine lineNumber="668"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00669" /><CodeLine lineNumber="669"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; This compiles to the same MUL + UMULH as GCC/Clang&#39;s &#95;&#95;uint128&#95;t method.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00670" /><CodeLine lineNumber="670"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00671" /><CodeLine lineNumber="671"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#elif defined(&#95;M&#95;ARM64) || defined(&#95;M&#95;ARM64EC)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00672" /><CodeLine lineNumber="672"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00673" /><CodeLine lineNumber="673"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#ifndef &#95;MSC&#95;VER</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00674" /><CodeLine lineNumber="674"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#pragma intrinsic(&#95;&#95;umulh)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00675" /><CodeLine lineNumber="675"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#endif</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00676" /><CodeLine lineNumber="676"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> r128;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="677"><span class="doxyHighlight">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = lhs &#42; rhs;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="678"><span class="doxyHighlight">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = &#95;&#95;umulh(lhs, rhs);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="679"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> r128;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="680"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="681"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#else</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="682"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="683"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; Portable scalar method. Optimized for 32-bit and 64-bit ALUs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; This is a fast and simple grade school multiply, which is shown below</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="686"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; with base 10 arithmetic instead of base 0x100000000.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="687"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="688"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;           9 3 // D2 lhs = 93</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="689"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;         x 7 5 // D2 rhs = 75</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="690"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     ----------</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="691"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;           1 5 // D2 lo&#95;lo = (93 % 10) &#42; (75 % 10) = 15</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="692"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;         4 5 | // D2 hi&#95;lo = (93 / 10) &#42; (75 % 10) = 45</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="693"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;         2 1 | // D2 lo&#95;hi = (93 % 10) &#42; (75 / 10) = 21</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="694"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     + 6 3 | | // D2 hi&#95;hi = (93 / 10) &#42; (75 / 10) = 63</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     ---------</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00696" /><CodeLine lineNumber="696"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;         2 7 | // D2 cross = (15 / 10) + (45 % 10) + 21 = 27</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00697" /><CodeLine lineNumber="697"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     + 6 7 | | // D2 upper = (27 / 10) + (45 / 10) + 63 = 67</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00698" /><CodeLine lineNumber="698"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     ---------</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00699" /><CodeLine lineNumber="699"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;       6 9 7 5 // D4 res = (27 &#42; 10) + (15 % 10) + (67 &#42; 100) = 6975</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00700" /><CodeLine lineNumber="700"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00701" /><CodeLine lineNumber="701"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; The reasons for adding the products like this are:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00702" /><CodeLine lineNumber="702"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;  1 It avoids manual carry tracking. Just like how</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00703" /><CodeLine lineNumber="703"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     (9 &#42; 9) + 9 + 9 = 99, the same applies with this for UINT64&#95;MAX.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00704" /><CodeLine lineNumber="704"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     This avoids a lot of complexity.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00705" /><CodeLine lineNumber="705"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00706" /><CodeLine lineNumber="706"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;  2 It hints for, and on Clang, compiles to, the powerful UMAAL</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00707" /><CodeLine lineNumber="707"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     instruction available in ARM&#39;s Digital Signal Processing extension</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00708" /><CodeLine lineNumber="708"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     in 32-bit ARMv6 and later, which is shown below:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="709"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;         void UMAAL(xxh&#95;u32 &#42;RdLo, xxh&#95;u32 &#42;RdHi, xxh&#95;u32 Rn, xxh&#95;u32 Rm)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;         &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;             uint64&#95;t product = (uint64&#95;t)&#42;RdLo &#42; (uint64&#95;t)&#42;RdHi + Rn + Rm;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;             &#42;RdLo = (xxh&#95;u32)(product &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;             &#42;RdHi = (xxh&#95;u32)(product &gt;&gt; 32);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;         &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     This instruction was designed for efficient long multiplication, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     allows this to be calculated in only 4 instructions at speeds</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     comparable to some 64-bit ALUs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="720"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00721" /><CodeLine lineNumber="721"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;  3 It isn&#39;t terrible on other platforms. Usually this will be a couple</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00722" /><CodeLine lineNumber="722"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;     of 32-bit ADD/ADCs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00723" /><CodeLine lineNumber="723"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00724" /><CodeLine lineNumber="724"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00725" /><CodeLine lineNumber="725"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; First calculate all of the cross products. &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00726" /><CodeLine lineNumber="726"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> lo&#95;lo = <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>(lhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF, rhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00727" /><CodeLine lineNumber="727"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> hi&#95;lo = <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>(lhs &gt;&gt; 32, rhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00728" /><CodeLine lineNumber="728"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> lo&#95;hi = <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>(lhs &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF, rhs &gt;&gt; 32);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00729" /><CodeLine lineNumber="729"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> hi&#95;hi = <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>(lhs &gt;&gt; 32, rhs &gt;&gt; 32);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00730" /><CodeLine lineNumber="730"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00731" /><CodeLine lineNumber="731"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; Now add the products together. These will never overflow. &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00732" /><CodeLine lineNumber="732"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> cross = (lo&#95;lo &gt;&gt; 32) + (hi&#95;lo &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF) + lo&#95;hi;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00733" /><CodeLine lineNumber="733"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> upper = (hi&#95;lo &gt;&gt; 32) + (cross &gt;&gt; 32) + hi&#95;hi;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00734" /><CodeLine lineNumber="734"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> lower = (cross &lt;&lt; 32) | (lo&#95;lo &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00735" /><CodeLine lineNumber="735"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00736" /><CodeLine lineNumber="736"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> r128;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00737" /><CodeLine lineNumber="737"><span class="doxyHighlight">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> = lower;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00738" /><CodeLine lineNumber="738"><span class="doxyHighlight">  r128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> = upper;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00739" /><CodeLine lineNumber="739"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> r128;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00740" /><CodeLine lineNumber="740"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#endif</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00741" /><CodeLine lineNumber="741"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00742" /><CodeLine lineNumber="742"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00743" /><CodeLine lineNumber="743"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;! Seems to produce slightly better code on GCC for some reason. &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00744" /><CodeLine lineNumber="744" lineLink="#aace3bad147eeed78a2f1cab33d506d59"><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/compiler-h/#a338bdf98e9e600f582b7bef274bc9388">LLVM&#95;ATTRIBUTE&#95;ALWAYS&#95;INLINE</a> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">constexpr</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint64&#95;t <a href="#aace3bad147eeed78a2f1cab33d506d59">XXH&#95;xorshift64</a>(uint64&#95;t v64,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00745" /><CodeLine lineNumber="745"><span class="doxyHighlight">                                                               </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">int</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> shift) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00746" /><CodeLine lineNumber="746"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> v64 ^ (v64 &gt;&gt; shift);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00747" /><CodeLine lineNumber="747"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00748" /><CodeLine lineNumber="748"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00802" /><CodeLine lineNumber="802" lineLink="#a68128490131d65e06f6066616f80ddf5"><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="#a68128490131d65e06f6066616f80ddf5">XXH3&#95;len&#95;9to16&#95;128b</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint8&#95;t &#42;input, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">size&#95;t</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> len, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint8&#95;t &#42;secret,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00803" /><CodeLine lineNumber="803"><span class="doxyHighlight">                    uint64&#95;t seed) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00804" /><CodeLine lineNumber="804"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> bitflipl =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00805" /><CodeLine lineNumber="805"><span class="doxyHighlight">      (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 32) ^ <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 40)) - seed;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00806" /><CodeLine lineNumber="806"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> bitfliph =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00807" /><CodeLine lineNumber="807"><span class="doxyHighlight">      (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 48) ^ <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(secret + 56)) + seed;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00808" /><CodeLine lineNumber="808"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> input&#95;lo = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(input);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00809" /><CodeLine lineNumber="809"><span class="doxyHighlight">  uint64&#95;t input&#95;hi = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/support/endian/#a0fa2f859066acd16820ab083040158c9">endian::read64le</a>(input + len - 8);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00810" /><CodeLine lineNumber="810"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> m128 =</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00811" /><CodeLine lineNumber="811"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="#a5a010401dcddb43e0a6fdcac9564d69b">XXH&#95;mult64to128</a>(input&#95;lo ^ input&#95;hi ^ bitflipl, <a href="#a502e23a6442aeb2e9d55069d0f600e7e">PRIME64&#95;1</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00812" /><CodeLine lineNumber="812"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00813" /><CodeLine lineNumber="813"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; Put len in the middle of m128 to ensure that the length gets mixed to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00814" /><CodeLine lineNumber="814"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; both the low and high bits in the 128x64 multiply below.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00815" /><CodeLine lineNumber="815"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00816" /><CodeLine lineNumber="816"><span class="doxyHighlight">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> += (uint64&#95;t)(len - 1) &lt;&lt; 54;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00817" /><CodeLine lineNumber="817"><span class="doxyHighlight">  input&#95;hi ^= bitfliph;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00818" /><CodeLine lineNumber="818"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00819" /><CodeLine lineNumber="819"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; Add the high 32 bits of input&#95;hi to the high 32 bits of m128, then</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00820" /><CodeLine lineNumber="820"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; add the long product of the low 32 bits of input&#95;hi and PRIME32&#95;2 to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00821" /><CodeLine lineNumber="821"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; the high 64 bits of m128.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00822" /><CodeLine lineNumber="822"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00823" /><CodeLine lineNumber="823"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; The best approach to this operation is different on 32-bit and 64-bit.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00824" /><CodeLine lineNumber="824"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00825" /><CodeLine lineNumber="825"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;) &lt; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(uint64&#95;t)) &#123; </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; 32-bit &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00826" /><CodeLine lineNumber="826"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00827" /><CodeLine lineNumber="827"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; 32-bit optimized version, which is more readable.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00828" /><CodeLine lineNumber="828"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00829" /><CodeLine lineNumber="829"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; On 32-bit, it removes an ADC and delays a dependency between the two</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00830" /><CodeLine lineNumber="830"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; halves of m128.high64, but it generates an extra mask on 64-bit.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00831" /><CodeLine lineNumber="831"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00832" /><CodeLine lineNumber="832"><span class="doxyHighlight">    m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> += (input&#95;hi &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF00000000ULL) +</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00833" /><CodeLine lineNumber="833"><span class="doxyHighlight">                   <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>((uint32&#95;t)input&#95;hi, <a href="#a6db4d465a9f3c93ce1369c017071c9fb">PRIME32&#95;2</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00834" /><CodeLine lineNumber="834"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00835" /><CodeLine lineNumber="835"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00836" /><CodeLine lineNumber="836"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; 64-bit optimized (albeit more confusing) version.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00837" /><CodeLine lineNumber="837"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00838" /><CodeLine lineNumber="838"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; Uses some properties of addition and multiplication to remove the mask:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00839" /><CodeLine lineNumber="839"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00840" /><CodeLine lineNumber="840"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; Let:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00841" /><CodeLine lineNumber="841"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;    a = input&#95;hi.lo = (input&#95;hi &amp; 0x00000000FFFFFFFF)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00842" /><CodeLine lineNumber="842"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;    b = input&#95;hi.hi = (input&#95;hi &amp; 0xFFFFFFFF00000000)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00843" /><CodeLine lineNumber="843"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;    c = PRIME32&#95;2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00844" /><CodeLine lineNumber="844"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00845" /><CodeLine lineNumber="845"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;    a + (b &#42; c)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00846" /><CodeLine lineNumber="846"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; Inverse Property: x + y - x == y</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00847" /><CodeLine lineNumber="847"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;    a + (b &#42; (1 + c - 1))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00848" /><CodeLine lineNumber="848"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; Distributive Property: x &#42; (y + z) == (x &#42; y) + (x &#42; z)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00849" /><CodeLine lineNumber="849"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;    a + (b &#42; 1) + (b &#42; (c - 1))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00850" /><CodeLine lineNumber="850"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; Identity Property: x &#42; 1 == x</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00851" /><CodeLine lineNumber="851"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;    a + b + (b &#42; (c - 1))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00852" /><CodeLine lineNumber="852"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00853" /><CodeLine lineNumber="853"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; Substitute a, b, and c:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00854" /><CodeLine lineNumber="854"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;    input&#95;hi.hi + input&#95;hi.lo + ((uint64&#95;t)input&#95;hi.lo &#42; (PRIME32&#95;2</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00855" /><CodeLine lineNumber="855"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; - 1))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00856" /><CodeLine lineNumber="856"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00857" /><CodeLine lineNumber="857"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42; Since input&#95;hi.hi + input&#95;hi.lo == input&#95;hi, we get this:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00858" /><CodeLine lineNumber="858"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;    input&#95;hi + ((uint64&#95;t)input&#95;hi.lo &#42; (PRIME32&#95;2 - 1))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00859" /><CodeLine lineNumber="859"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">     &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00860" /><CodeLine lineNumber="860"><span class="doxyHighlight">    m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a> += input&#95;hi + <a href="#a08f3f09f1c097e41499563c7468d031c">XXH&#95;mult32to64</a>((uint32&#95;t)input&#95;hi, <a href="#a6db4d465a9f3c93ce1369c017071c9fb">PRIME32&#95;2</a> - 1);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00861" /><CodeLine lineNumber="861"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00862" /><CodeLine lineNumber="862"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; m128 ^= XXH&#95;swap64(m128 &gt;&gt; 64); &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00863" /><CodeLine lineNumber="863"><span class="doxyHighlight">  m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a> ^= <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a2a584ab307c8e962527df226089a7470">byteswap</a>(m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#af6ae9edb7b299ab65fcbc7eca03b381a">high64</a>);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00864" /><CodeLine lineNumber="864"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00865" /><CodeLine lineNumber="865"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42; 128x64 multiply: h128 = m128 &#42; PRIME64&#95;2; &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00866" /><CodeLine lineNumber="866"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t">XXH128&#95;hash&#95;t</a> h128 = <a href="#a5a010401dcddb43e0a6fdcac9564d69b">XXH&#95;mult64to128</a>(m128.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/xxh128-hash-t/#a994e5b99d3dceafee44f8c983d75103b">low64</a>, <a href="#a713d2b3b0b93699da8b5140e49ae0724">PRIME64&#95;2</a>);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00948" /><CodeLine lineNumber="948"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;  We set as &#96;i&#96; as offset + 32 We do this so that unchanged</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00949" /><CodeLine lineNumber="949"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; &#96;len&#96; can be used as upper bound. This reaches a sweet spot</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00950" /><CodeLine lineNumber="950"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; where both x86 and aarch64 get simple agen and good codegen</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00951" /><CodeLine lineNumber="951"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; for the loop.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00952" /><CodeLine lineNumber="952"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;/</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00953" /><CodeLine lineNumber="953"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (i = 32; i &lt; 160; i += 32) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00954" /><CodeLine lineNumber="954"><span class="doxyHighlight">    acc = <a href="#a2fa22ae762463bb383e63bd381952344">XXH128&#95;mix32B</a>(acc, input + i - 32, input + i - 16, secret + i - 32,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00955" /><CodeLine lineNumber="955"><span class="doxyHighlight">                        seed);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00956" /><CodeLine lineNumber="956"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00957" /><CodeLine lineNumber="957"><span class="doxyHighlight">  acc.low64 = <a href="#a5f41b833306622b3b79b209e3829bbb1">XXH3&#95;avalanche</a>(acc.low64);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00958" /><CodeLine lineNumber="958"><span class="doxyHighlight">  acc.high64 = <a href="#a5f41b833306622b3b79b209e3829bbb1">XXH3&#95;avalanche</a>(acc.high64);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00959" /><CodeLine lineNumber="959"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00960" /><CodeLine lineNumber="960"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; NB: &#96;i &lt;= len&#96; will duplicate the last 32-bytes if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00961" /><CodeLine lineNumber="961"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42; len % 32 was zero. This is an unfortunate necessity to keep</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00963" /><CodeLine lineNumber="963"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">   &#42;/</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00970" /><CodeLine lineNumber="970"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="#a2fa22ae762463bb383e63bd381952344">XXH128&#95;mix32B</a>(acc, input + len - 16, input + len - 32,</span></CodeLine>
